Package: easystroke
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: X11 gesture recognition application
 Easystroke is a gesture-recognition application for X11 that allows users
 to control their desktop using mouse gestures. It is written in C++ using
 GTKmm 3.0 and integrates deeply with X11 for input handling.
 .
 Features include:
  * Mouse gesture recognition with configurable sensitivity
  * Action execution based on recognized gestures
  * Application-specific gesture contexts
  * Visual feedback during gesture input
  * Comprehensive configuration interface
 .
 This is the community-maintained fork that has been updated to work
 with modern Ubuntu distributions (Noble 24.04+).